Author lib. 1. de Mirab. Scrip.
Apud Aug. c. 21. where we muſt take notice, with the Authour of the Memorable things of the holy Scripture, that it was not without miracle, men and Children, and the reſt of the people hearing every verſe but once, did yet faithfully repeat the ſame after Moſes, whoſe voice could not be heard of all. However it were, they ſpake all with one heart and voice, or rather with millions of voices which came but from one and the ſame Source, and from a like Spirit which animated ſo many lungs and mouths.

